# Payment Import Feature Plan

**Feature:** [Onboarding] Import Pagos / cartola / cobranzas históricas

**Goal:** Allow admins to import historical payment data (payments, collections) from legacy system during onboarding. Payments are matched to invoices/boletas, reducing pending balances and enabling accurate collections tracking.

**Scope:** Backend (xlsx parser, validation, transactional import, idempotency) + Frontend (migration tab UI, template download, preview, reporting)

## Tasks

### Task 1: Database model for payment imports
Create Payment model and migration to track imported payments with reconciliation support.
- Model: Payment with fields (fecha_pago, rut_cliente, monto, medio_pago, referencia, folio_documento, tipo_documento, estado)
- Migration: Alembic migration to add payments table
- Tests: Model validation, relationships to Invoice/Boleta/Customer

### Task 2: Excel parser and validation layer
Implement xlsx parsing with comprehensive validation and error reporting.
- Parse xlsx with openpyxl
- Validate columns (fecha_pago, rut_cliente, monto, medio_pago, referencia, folio_documento, tipo_documento)
- Type validation and error collection
- Preview data structures

### Task 3: Payment matching and application logic
Implement business logic to match payments to documents and apply them.
- Match by folio_documento + tipo_documento
- Apply payment amount to invoice/boleta, reducing pending_amount
- Handle payment without document reference (pago a cuenta)
- Validate sum(pagos) <= total_documento (detect overpayment)
- Idempotency: prevent duplicate imports of same Excel

### Task 4: Transactional import backend
Create API endpoint for transactional import with rollback and per-row error reporting.
- GET /api/onboarding/payments/template - download template xlsx
- POST /api/onboarding/payments/preview - validate and preview
- POST /api/onboarding/payments/import - execute transactional import
- Error handling: rollback on fatal, report per-row for recoverable
- Generate import report (created/updated/pending/error count + details)

### Task 5: Frontend migration tab UI
Add payment import section to admin onboarding migration tab.
- Section: "Historial de Pagos"
- Template download button
- File upload with validation feedback
- Preview table (rows valid/invalid)
- Progress feedback during import
- Report display (downloadable, sortable by status)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Payments can be imported from Excel template with all specified columns
- [ ] Invalid rows are reported with specific error reasons
- [ ] Valid payments are applied to invoices/boletas, reducing pending balance
- [ ] Import is transactional (all succeed or all rollback)
- [ ] Re-running same Excel doesn't duplicate payments (idempotent)
- [ ] Payments without referenced document are recorded as "pago a cuenta"
- [ ] Overpayment validation detects and reports when sum(pagos) > document total
- [ ] Import report is downloadable
- [ ] Frontend UI matches existing design system (Modal, danger colors where needed)
- [ ] Tests: 80%+ coverage for parser, matching, API endpoints

## Context
- Use existing Payment model (if exists) or create new
- Integrates with Invoice/Boleta/Customer models
- Onboarding flow is admin-only (role check)
- Must maintain idempotency (same file, same result)
